Implemented Vercel Speed Insights for React/Vite project

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
1. **frontend/package.json**
   - Added `@vercel/speed-insights` version ^2.0.0 as a dependency

2. **frontend/package-lock.json**
   - Updated lockfile with @vercel/speed-insights and its 320 sub-dependencies

3. **frontend/src/App.jsx**
   - Imported `SpeedInsights` component from `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
   - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the root level of the App component
   - Component is placed within the main div, ensuring it tracks all pages/routes

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite applications:
- Used the React-specific import path (`@vercel/speed-insights/react`)
- Placed the component at the root level to ensure tracking across all routes
- No additional configuration needed - the component automatically collects performance metrics

## Build & Linting Results
- ✅ Build completed successfully (vite build)
- ✅ No new linting errors introduced in App.jsx
- ✅ All changes pass validation

## Next Steps (For Project Owner)
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel project dashboard
2. Deploy the changes to Vercel
3. Wait several days for visitor data to accumulate
4. View analytics in the Vercel dashboard

The Speed Insights will automatically start collecting Web Vitals and performance metrics once deployed to Vercel.
